+{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_01DxB1rLtix48GbzXwnFZG5v","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Interesting! It connects but never receives the message. The difference between the debug test (which works) and debug2 (which doesn't) is:\n- debug: creates the app inline and uses `new WebSocket(...)` directly with message handler inline\n- debug2: uses `connectWs` function which returns after `'open'`, then separately calls `waitForMessage`\n\nThe problem is a **race condition**: the sync message is sent by the server immediately on connection. By the time the `open` event fires and we return from `connectWs`, and THEN set up the `once('message')` handler, the message has already been received and missed.\n\nIn the debug test, I set up the `on('message')` handler before connecting, so it catches the message. In the `connectWs` pattern, the message handler is set up after the open event resolves.\n\nThe fix: I need to set up the message listener before the connection opens. Let me restructure the test helper."}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1288,"cache_read_input_tokens":58911,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":1288},"output_tokens":2,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"ba7df0fd-2045-4133-bb4c-31b7b7df73af","uuid":"ea503278-4e7d-4f81-9ca1-b8eecf77a57d"}
